!-----THIS IS COMMON/INCLUDE FILE DPCOZZ.INC-----
!     THIS IS THE PRIMARY COMMON FOR DIMENSION REDUCTION VIA SCRATCH AREA
!
!     UPDATED--AUGUST      1990. MOVE IGARB0 SETTING TO DPCOPA.INC
!     UPDATED--MAY         1995. 10 ADDITIONAL ARRAYS FOR DPFIT.
!     UPDATED--JULY        2019. COMBINE DPCOZZ AND DPCOZ2 INTO A
!                                SINGLE SCRATCH STORAGE AREA.
!     UPDATED--JULY        2019. REDEFINE IGARB0 TO BE 35*MAXOBV
!                                IN DPCOPA.INC
!
!  THIS INCLUDE FILE CREATES A COMMON BLOCK FOR "SCRATCH" STORAGE.
!  MANY DATAPLOT ROUTINES DIMENSION TEMPORARY ARRAYS OF SIZE MAXOBV
!  (MAXIMUM NUMBER OF OBSERVATIONS FOR A VARIABLE) AND MAXPOP (MAXIMUM
!  NUMBER OF POINTS PER PLOT).  AS MAXOBV AND MAXPOP ARE ADJUSTED
!  UPWARD, THE SIZE OF THE DATAPLOT EXECUTABLE FILE EXPANDS RAPIDLY.
!  THE PURPOSE OF THIS COMMON BLOCK IS TO ALLOW "MAXOBV" TO BE INCREASED
!  WITHOUT DRASTICALLY INCREASING THE SIZE OF DATAPLOT'S EXECUTABLE FILE.
!
!  NOTE THAT THESE ARE THE ONLY INCLUDE FILES THAT ARE NOT PLACED IN
!  THE MAIN ROUTINE.  NORMALLY, COMMON BLOCKS SHOULD BE PLACED IN THE MAIN
!  ROUTINE TO ENSURE THAT THEY GET LOADED IN THE "ROOT" SEGMENT ON SYSTEMS
!  THAT USE SEGMENTATION OR OVERLAYING.  THIS PREVENTS COMMON BLOCKS FROM
!  LOSING THEIR VALUES WHEN SEGMENTS ARE SWAPPED.   HOWEVER, SINCE THESE
!  COMMON BLOCKS ARE SIMPLY PROVIDING SCRATCH SPACE, THIS DOES NOT MATTER.
!  IN FACT, IT IS DESIRABLE TO HAVE THEM PLACED AS FAR DOWN THE SEGMENTATION
!  SCHEME AS POSSIBLE.
!
!  THE INCLUDE FILES "DPCOZI" AND "DPCOZD" PROVIDE SIMILAR SCRATCH SPACE
!  FOR INTEGER AND DOUBLE PRECISION ARRAYS.
!
!  THE FOLLOWING ROUTINES USE THE SCATCH SPACE:
!
!  A) MOST OF THE ROUTINES CALLED BY MAINAN AND MAINGR USE SCRATCH ARRAYS.
!     TYPICALLY, MOST USE BETWEEN ONE AND EIGHT ARRAYS DIMENSIONED TO MAXOBV.
!     SINCE THESE ROUTINES DO NOT DEPEND ON THE OLD VALUES IN THE TEMPORARY
!     ARRAYS, THERE SHOLD BE NO PROBLEM WITH CONFLICTING USE OF THE
!     SCRATCH SPACE.  ALSO, ONCE THE COORDINATES ARE CALCULATED BY A
!     MAINGR ROUTINE, THE SCRATCH SPACE CAN BE REUSED BY THE ACTUAL
!     GRAPHING ROUTINES.
!
!     THE FOLLOWING ROUTINES ARE THE ONLY ONES USING MORE THAN 8 ARRAYS.
!
!     1) DPYATE - THIS ROUTINE USES 17 REAL ARRAYS (AND 3 INTEGER ARRAYS)
!     2) DPFIT  - THIS ROUTINE USES 10 REAL ARRAYS.  IN ADDITION, IT USES
!        USES ONE ARRAY DIMENSIONED TO (MAXOBV,MAXCMF) WHERE MAXCMF IS THE
!        MAXIMUM NUMBER OF VARIABLES FOR A FIT (THE DEFAULT VALUE IS 35).
!        THIS MEANS FIT REQUIRES (10+MAXCMF)*MAXOBV WORDS OF SCRATCH SPACE
!        (OR 45*MAXOBV FOR THE DEFAULT VALUE OF MAXCMF).
!     3) DPDEXP - THIS ROUTINE USES 4 ARRAYS DIMENSIONED TO 10*MAXOBV FOR
!        A TOTAL OF 40*MAXOBV WORDS.  ALSO, FOR FUTURE DEVELOPMENT, ALLOW
!        FOR 5 ADDITIONAL ARRAYS (IT USES ONE NOW).  THIS REQUIRES 45*MAXOBV
!        WORDS OF SCRATCH SPACE.
!
! B) SOME OF THE MATHEMATICS ROUTINES UNDER  THE LET COMMAND ALSO USE SCRATCH
!    SPACE.  MORE CARE NEEDS TO BE TAKEN WITH THESE ROUTINES SINCE THEY CAN
!    POTENTIALLY BE CALLED BY ANALYSIS AND GRAPHICS COMMANDS.  TO AVOID
!    POSSIBLE STORAGE CONFLICTS, DPMATC AND DPSTAC SHOULD USE ARRAYS 1
!    THROUGH 10 (THESE ROUTINES EXECUTE THE MATH AND STAT COMMANDS UNDER
!    LET AND WILL NOT BE CALLED BY MAINGR AND MAINAN ROUTINES).  THE
!    UNDERLYING ROUTINES CAN USE 11 THROUGH 45.  FOR SAFETY, THEY USE 41
!    THROUGH 45.  THE ONLY EXCEPTION IS THE INTERP ROUTINE, WHICH NEEDS 17
!    ARRAYS.  IT USES 11 THROUGH 27.  HOWEVER, THIS ROUTINE WILL NOT BE
!    CALLED BY THE MAINGR OR MAINAN ROUTINES, SO THERE SHOULD NOT BE A
!    CONFLICT.  ALSO, DPYATE, DPFIT, AND DPDEXP WERE MANUALLY SEARCHED TO
!    ENSURE THAT THEY DO NOT CALL UNDERLYING LET ROUTINES THAT MIGHT CAUSE
!    A STORAGE CONFLICT.
!
! C) THE ROUTINES THAT DO THE ACTUAL PLOTTING ALSO USE SCRATCH ARRAYS.  THE
!    DISCRETE GRAPHICS ARE DONE BEFORE ANY OF THE CONTINUOUS GRAPHICS, SO
!    THAT SPACE CAN BE SAFELY REUSED.  THE PLOTGE ROUTINE (WHICH IS THE
!    ROUTINE THAT INITIATES THE ACTUAL PLOTTING ON CONTINUOUS DEVICES)
!    USES 12 ARRAYS DIMENSIONED TO MAXPOP.  THESE SHOULD NOT BE REUSED
!    UNTIL THE SPECIFIC GRAPH IS COMPLETED).  THE UNDERLYING GRAPHICS USE
!    AN ADDITIONAL 6 ARRAYS (ALTHOUGH IT MIGHT BE POSSIBLE TO OVERLAY SOME
!    OF THESE, IT SEEMS SAFER TO USE SEPARATE STORAGE).  IN SUMMARY, THE
!    ACTUAL GRAPHING ROUTINES REQUIRE 18*MAXPOP WORDS OF SCRATCH SPACE.
!
! IN SUMMARY, THE AMOUNT OF SCRATCH SPACE REQUIRED (IN WORDS) IS THE
! MAXIMUM OF THE FOLLOWING 3 NUMBERS.  THE VALUE OF IGARB0 SHOULD BE SET
! TO THIS.
!
!    45*MAXOBV
!    (10+MAXCMF)*MAXOBV
!    18*MAXPOP
!
! ALTHOUGH LOGICALLY A SINGLE COMMON BLOCK COULD BE USED, IT IS PROBABLY
! DESIRABLE TO REDUCE THE SIZE OF INDIVIDUAL COMMON BLOCKS BY SPLITTING
! THE COMMON BLOCK INTO SEVERAL SMALLER ONES.  HOWEVER, THE ABILITY TO
! DO THIS IS LIMITED BY THE FACT THAT THE FIT ROUTINE DIMENSIONS A SINGLE
! ARRAY TO MAXCMF*MAXOBV (I.E., 35 X 2048 BY DEFAULT) AND IT IS NOT LEGAL
! TO EQUIVALENCE A SINGLE ARRAY OVER MORE THAN ONE COMMON BLOCK.  THE
! COMMON BLOCK WILL BE SPLIT INTO 2 PARTS.  MOST OF THE ROUTINES WILL
! ONLY USE THE FIRST PART.  CURRENTLY, ONLY ABOUT A DOZEN ROUTINES NEED
! THE SECOND ONE.
!
!     INCLUDE FILE          SIZE
!     ============          ====
!OLD  DPCOZZ                MAX OF 10*MAXOBV, 5*MAXPOP
!NEW  DPCOZZ                MAX OF 66*MAXOBV, 5*MAXPOP
!
